LORE midgaard-criminal
FLAGS MIDGAARD CRIMINAL
Outer ward unlicensed operations exist past the second ring road where
Guild Concordat enforcement doesn't reach
The Unindexed Years represent both a cover-up and an opportunity: certain
sealed records can prove or destroy inheritance claims; the right buyer
pays well for either confirmation or destruction
Gloamvault access routes are known to specific criminal networks; used
to bypass gate checkpoints; the city doesn't map them officially
Reckoning faction members sometimes need deniable investigators; they
pay in information, not coin; the information is often worth more
Lantern Watch is when guard density is highest; plan activity accordingly;
Ash Watch (curfew) sees ward inspectors, not patrol guards — different
vulnerabilities
Stolen arms: all city gates check manifests against known stolen-arms lists;
selling in Midgaard requires either clean provenance or a cooperative fence
~
